<h1 class="govuk-heading-m">Data in DfE Services</h1>
<p class="govuk-body">
  DfE services use many common datasets, including countries, schools, local authorities and teacher training providers.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
  This site helps teams:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>find existing datasets before creating new ones</li>
  <li>understand where authoritative data is maintained</li>
  <li>use consistent data across services</li>
  <li>reduce duplication and maintenance effort</li>
  <li>improve analytical consistency across DfE services</li>
</ul>
<p class="govuk-body">
  The guidance is intended for:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>developers</li>
  <li>technical architects</li>
  <li>business analysts</li>
  <li>product managers</li>
  <li>delivery managers</li>
  <li>analysts</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Why data matters?</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  There are many reasons why data is important:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>
    Analytics reports are used to make decisions, and quality data makes analytics more accurate.
  </li>
  <li>
    Some datasets are static (reference data) or almost static (almost reference data). Those datasets should have a single source, and be well documented.
  </li>
  <li>
    When every service uses the same lists, data can be joined and compared across services without costly mapping and cleaning.
  </li>
  <li>
    Consistent, well-defined values make forms clearer for users and reduce input errors.
  </li>
  <li>
    Reusing existing datasets saves teams from building and maintaining duplicate copies that drift out of date.
  </li>
</ul>
<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Before Creating a Dataset</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Before creating or maintaining your own dataset:
</p>
<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
  <li>Check the Data Lists.</li>
  <li>Identify whether an authoritative source already exists.</li>
  <li>Review the available guidance.</li>
  <li>Contact the SD Data Insights Team if you are unsure which dataset to use.</li>
</ol>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Many DfE services use similar datasets. Reusing existing data sources improves consistency, reduces duplicate maintenance and supports more reliable reporting and analysis.
</p>
<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Types of Data</h2>
<h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Reference Data</h3>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Reference data consists of standard datasets that can be reused across multiple services.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Examples include:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>Countries and Territories</li>
  <li>HESA Domiciles</li>
  <li>Qualifications</li>
  <li>Degree Data</li>
  <li>Subject Specialisms</li>
  <li>Equality and Diversity Data</li>
  <li>Bank Holidays</li>
</ul>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Reference data is available through the DfE Reference Data Lists.
</p>
<h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Other Datasets</h3>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Some commonly used datasets are maintained by specialist teams or individual services and are not currently part of the DfE Reference Data Lists.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Guidance for these datasets is available within this site.
</p>
<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How to Use This Site</h2>
<h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Data Lists</h3>
<p class="govuk-body">
  Use the Data Lists to:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>discover available datasets</li>
  <li>identify authoritative sources</li>
  <li>understand which dataset is appropriate for your use case</li>
  <li>find links to source data and supporting guidance</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">SD Data Insights Team</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
  The SD Data Insights Team provides guidance on shared datasets used across DfE digital services.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
  We can help when:
</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li>a dataset appears incorrect</li>
  <li>a dataset is missing</li>
  <li>you need guidance on using existing data</li>
  <li>you are unsure which dataset is appropriate</li>
  <li>you would like a dataset reviewed for inclusion within the DfE Reference Data Lists</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Support</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">
  If you have a question or suggestion, contact the SD Data Insights Team.
</p>
<p class="govuk-body">
  The team welcomes feedback on datasets, guidance and opportunities to improve consistency across DfE services.
</p>